    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the art and architecture that coincided with the regin of Selim II. The Selimiye Mosque was built for him by Sinan between 1570 and 1574.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000012651/Du Ry, Art of Islam (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de kunst en architectuur in de periode van de heerschappij van Selim II. Sinan bouwde tussen 1570 en 1574 voor hem de Selimiye-moskee.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用來表示與賽里姆二世統治時期有關的藝術與建築。建築師希南（Selim）於西元 1570 年至 1574年間為賽里姆二世建造了賽里米耶清真寺（Selimiye Mosque）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
